  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the oven to 375°F (190°C).",
    "In a large bowl, mix together the roasted peanuts, brown rice flour, cocoa powder, dried dates, coconut oil, salt, black pepper, garlic powder, and smoked paprika until well combined.",
    "Press the mixture into a 9x9-inch baking dish.",
    "Bake for 25 minutes or until the edges are golden brown and the center is set.",
    "Remove from the oven and let cool completely before slicing into squares."
